ash<\/li>\n<li>Pin Missile<\/li>\n<li>Earthquake<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Bug Buzz<\/li>\n<li>Heat Wave<\/li>\n<li>Wild Charge<\/li>\n<li>Quiver Dance<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Bug Bite<\/li>\n<li>Bullet Punch<\/li>\n<li>Dual Wingbeat<\/li>\n<li>Swords Dance<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Earthquake<\/li>\n<li>Dragon Claw<\/li>\n<li>Rock Slide<\/li>\n<li>Crunch<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\">\n<table class=\"table grey left aligntop collapsed\" style=\"min-width:1000px;\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"6\" class=\"text-large left\">Gym Leader Benjamin (Insane)<br \/>\n            <span class=\"table-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"toggle-link\">[show]<\/a><\/span>\n            <\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th><\/th>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/araquanid.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/magnezone.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/rhyperior.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/volcarona.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/scizor-mega.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/flygon.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Araquanid Lv. 61<\/td>\n<td>Magnezone Lv. 62<\/td>\n<td>Rhyperior Lv. 62<\/td>\n<td>Volcarona Lv. 61<\/td>\n<td>Scizor (Mega) Lv. 62<\/td>\n<td>Flygon Lv. 62<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Water \/ Bug<\/td>\n<td>Electric \/ Steel<\/td>\n<td>Ground \/ Rock<\/td>\n<td>Bug \/ Fire<\/td>\n<td>Bug \/ Steel<\/td>\n<td>Ground \/ Dragon<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Weaknesses<\/th>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Flying (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Electric (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Rock (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Ground (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Fighting (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Fire (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Water (4x)<\/li>\n<li>Grass (4x)<\/li>\n<li>Ice (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Fighting (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Ground (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Steel (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Rock (4x)<\/li>\n<li>Flying (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Water (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Fire (4x)<\/li>\n<li>Fighting (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Ground (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Ice (4x)<\/li>\n<li>Dragon (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Fairy (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Held Item<\/th>\n<td>Sitrus Berry<\/td>\n<td>Eviolite<\/td>\n<td>Eviolite<\/td>\n<td>Eviolite<\/td>\n<td>Scizorite<\/td>\n<td>Life Orb<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Moves<\/th>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Liquidation<\/li>\n<li>Leech Fang<\/li>\n<li>Mirror Coat<\/li>\n<li>Sticky Web<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Thunderbolt<\/li>\n<li>Flash Cannon<\/li>\n<li>Hidden Power Fire<\/li>\n<li>Mirror Coat<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Earthquake<\/li>\n<li>Rock Blast<\/li>\n<li>Thunder Fang<\/li>\n<li>Counter<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Bug Buzz<\/li>\n<li>Overheat<\/li>\n<li>Wild Charge<\/li>\n<li>Quiver Dance<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Bug Bite<\/li>\n<li>Bullet Punch<\/li>\n<li>Dual Wingbeat<\/li>\n<li>Swords Dance<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Earthquake<\/li>\n<li>Clanging Scales<\/li>\n<li>Heat Wave<\/li>\n<li>Crunch<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>The Redwood Village Gym features special conditions based on the story of Benjamin Butterfree: when a Pok\u00e9mon\u2019s HP bar is depleted in battle, it devolves instead of fainting as normal. <\/p>\n<p>When a Pokemon reaches its base stage and cannot devolve any further, it faints. Once devolved, Pokemon will be unable to use any moves from their set which require evolution. Mega Evolutions in this Gym do not count as an additional evolution and will be treated as the normal evolved form of a Pokemon. <\/p>\n<h2>Redwood Gym Puzzle (Step-by-Step)<\/h2>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/02-pokemon-unbound-gym-entrance-redwood-village.jpg\" alt=\"Gym entrance \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Gym entrance<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>The Redwood Gym features a relatively straightforward puzzle. At the entrance, you\u2019ll find 4 separate rooms, each hosting a rock with a button. The goal here is to figure out the correct sequence in which the buttons must be pressed. <\/p>\n<p>Doing this successfully reveals a hidden room leading to the Gym Leader. Here\u2019s how you can solve the puzzle quickly. <\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 1:<\/strong> From the entrance, head into the third room from the left (pictured below)<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/03-pokemon-unbound-path-to-1st-room.jpg\" alt=\"Path to first room \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path to first room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>A Trainer hides behind this door and will trigger a battle as soon as you enter. <\/p>\n<table class=\"table grey left even-2col img125-1stcol\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\" class=\"text-large center\">Expert Tizzy<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/04-pokemon-unbound-expert-tizzy.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/yanmega.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Yanmega Lv. 58<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Bug \/ Flying<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Afterward, press the button on the rock directly next to the Trainer and make your way back to the entrance.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/05-pokemon-unbound-location-of-1st-button.jpg\" alt=\"Location of first button \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Location of first button<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 2:<\/strong> Now, head into the room on the far-left. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/06-pokemon-unbound-path-to-2nd-room.jpg\" alt=\"Path to second room \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path to second room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>You\u2019ll have to go through another Trainer battle here.<\/p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\">\n<table class=\"table grey left img125-1stcol\" style=\"min-width:400px;\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"3\" class=\"text-large center\">Ace Trainer Daisy<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/07-pokemon-unbound-ace-trainer-daisy.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/accelgor.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/scolipede.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Accelgor Lv. 58<\/td>\n<td>Scolipede Lv. 58<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Bug<\/td>\n<td>Bug \/ Poison<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<p>Once that\u2019s done, activate the button on the rock and head back to the entrance.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/08-pokemon-unbound-location-of-2nd-button.jpg\" alt=\"Location of second button \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Location of second button<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 3:<\/strong> Enter the room on the far-right. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/09-pokemon-unbound-path-to-3rd-room.jpg\" alt=\"Path to third room \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path to third room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Complete the Trainer battle in this room. <\/p>\n<table class=\"table grey left even-2col img125-1stcol\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\" class=\"text-large center\">Bug Catcher Curtis<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/10-pokemon-unbound-bug-catcher-curtis.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/beedrill.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Beedrill Lv. 58<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Bug \/ Flying<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>After the fight, press the button situated on the rock and head back outside.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/11-pokemon-unbound-location-of-3rd-button.jpg\" alt=\"Location of third button \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Location of third button<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 4:<\/strong> Lastly, go into the final room you haven\u2019t entered yet (second from the left).<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/12-pokemon-unbound-path-to-final-room.jpg\" alt=\"Path to final room \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path to final room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Battle your last Trainer here.<\/p>\n<table class=\"table grey left even-2col img125-1stcol\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\" class=\"text-large center\">Ninja Boy Fuller<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/13-pokemon-unbound-ninja-boy-fuller.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/ariados.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Ariados Lv. 58<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Bug \/ Poison<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>Then press the button on the rock and go back to the entrance.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/14-pokemon-unbound-location-of-final-button.jpg\" alt=\"Location of final button \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Location of final button<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 5:<\/strong> The hidden room leading to Benjamin will now be revealed. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/15-pokemon-unbound-secret-5th-room-revealed.jpg\" alt=\"Secret fifth room revealed \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Secret fifth room revealed<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/16-pokemon-unbound-benjamin-battle-room.jpg\" alt=\"Benjamin battle room \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Benjamin battle room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h2>Tips for Defeating Benjamin<\/h2>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/17-pokemon-unbound-benjamin-gym-battle.jpg\" alt=\"Benjamin Gym battle \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Benjamin Gym battle<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Use a Diverse Team:<\/strong> Benjamin is a surprisingly easy Gym Leader with multiple countering strategies and minimal restrictions. However, it\u2019s important to use a well-rounded team that features multiple types of Pokemon so you can effectively counter him.<\/p>\n<p>The ideal strategy is to include at least 1 strong Pokemon of each of the following types: Fire, Rock, Ground, and Electric. This team composition ensures perfect offense and defense against Benjamin. <\/p>\n<p><strong>Focus on Scizor:<\/strong> The only real danger posed by Benjamin is his Mega Scizor. It has both offensive and defensive moves in its arsenal and can pack a huge punch if given the opportunity. Additionally, Benjamin is highly likely to use a Max Potion on Scizor when its HP falls below the 50% mark.<\/p>\n<p>Since Scizor is a Bug \/ Steel-type, it\u2019s super weak to Fire-type moves (4x). Considering this, any strong Fire-type Pokemon (e.g Emboar) should be more than enough to handle it. If you don\u2019t plan on using a Fire-type, plan your strategy accordingly because Mega Scizor will surely pose a challenge.<\/p>\n<h2>Pokemon Team Suggestions<\/h2>\n<p>If you want to catch a couple of Pokemon that can be effective against Benjamin, here are some recommendations that can be found on nearby routes:<\/p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\">\n<table class=\"table grey left img125-1stcol\" style=\"min-width:400px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th><\/th>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/mudsdale.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/tranquill.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Mudsdale<\/td>\n<td>Tranquill<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Ground<\/td>\n<td>Normal \/ Flying<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Location<\/th>\n<td>Magnolia Field<\/td>\n<td>Magnolia Field<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<h2>Rewards<\/h2>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/benjamin\/18-pokemon-unbound-obtaining-the-time-badge.jpg\" alt=\"Obtaining the Time Badge \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Obtaining the Time Badge<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Defeating Benjamin rewards you with the following:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>\u20bd 9,600<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/tms-hms\/tm049-leech-fang\/\">TM49 Leech Fang<\/a><\/li>\n<li>Time Badge &#8211; Makes all Pokemon obey your commands. It also allows the use of <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/tms-hms\/hm05-dive\/\">HM05 Dive<\/a> outside of battle, allowing you to go underwater in suitable locations.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n        <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/gyms\/\" class=\"parent-page-card\">\n            <picture class=\"card-img\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/exterior-crater-town-gym.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/exterior-crater-town-gym.jpg 400w, https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/exterior-crater-town-gym-200x200.jpg 200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" \/>\t\t\t\t            <\/picture>\n            <span class=\"card-info\">\n                <span class=\"card-info__caption\">Back to:<\/span>\n                <strong class=\"wiki-title\">Gyms<\/strong>\n            <\/span>\n        <\/a>\n\n\t\t\n","protected":false},"featured_media":2601,"parent":2584,"menu_order":2,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false},"categories":[],"class_list":["post-2600","wiki","type-wiki","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/2600","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/wiki"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/2584"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.co